<!-- 05 BRAND-SPECIFIC NOTES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Brand-specific drain notes</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Quick reference for the brands we see most.</h2>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Bosch / Thermador.</strong> Filter twist-locks counter-clockwise from the bottom of the tub. E22 = filter clog, E24 = drain pump or hose. Bosch 800-series and Thermador share the same drain pump architecture.</li>
      <li><strong>KitchenAid / Whirlpool / Maytag.</strong> Filter is a two-piece assembly (upper screen plus cylindrical lower). F9E1 = drain failure. KitchenAid 2014-2019 models have a known drain pump fatigue pattern at year 6 to 8.</li>
      <li><strong>Samsung.</strong> 5C / 5E error codes confirm drain failure. StormWash and DW-series share drain pump platform.</li>
      <li><strong>LG.</strong> OE error code is the standard drain-failure code. Most LG drain pumps are direct-drive with a conical filter that traps debris efficiently but clogs from mineral buildup faster in SoCal hard water.</li>
      <li><strong>Miele.</strong> Filter is a multi-stage triangular tray system. F11 = drain failure, F12 = water inlet. Miele drain pumps have the longest service life of the major brands (year 10 to 14 typical) but are more expensive when they do fail.</li>
      <li><strong>GE Profile / Café.</strong> Older units use beep code patterns; newer GDT/ZDT show numeric codes. Drain pump replacement on Café series requires bottom-front access, slightly longer labor time.</li>
      <li><strong>Cove.</strong> Sub-Zero Group. Premium dishwasher line. Drain pump platform shared with select Bosch generations, so parts pipeline is reliable.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 REPAIR VS REPLACE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Repair vs replace</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">When the math tilts toward replacement.</h2>

    <p>Under 8 years old with drain pump failure, repair almost always. $260 to $440 for the pump buys 6 to 8 more years of operation on a unit that originally cost $800 to $3,500.</p>

    <p>8 to 12 years old, depends on price tier. Mid-tier units (under $1,200 original) start tilting toward replacement when the repair quote crosses $400, especially if other components are showing wear. Premium and luxury units (Bosch 800-series, Miele, Thermador, Cove, KitchenAid premium) almost always repair through year 12 to 15 because the chassis outlasts the components and replacement runs $1,800 to $3,500+ before installation.</p>

    <p>12+ years on mid-tier with cascading failures (drain pump plus heating element plus control board within months) is replacement territory. We tell you straight when that's the right call instead of charging you for a repair that's bridging a unit on its way out.</p>
  </div>
</section>

